cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.SC 

The paper deals with equational reasoning about morphisms of monoidal categories using string diagrams, which is a topic in category theory and logic (cs.LO). It also involves the use of software proof assistants (cs.PL) and context-free graph grammars (cs.CG) for automation. The manipulation of string diagrams involves graph rewriting (cs.DS) and the paper discusses decidability properties (cs.SC) of the framework for software implementation.
